1
00:00:07,255 --> 00:00:09,116
[The Love Delusion?]

2
00:00:10,053 --> 00:00:18,179
Many things that we value
are not objectively verifiable—

3
00:00:18,739 --> 00:00:20,900
like humour,
 

4
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:23,521
like what we like things
that are funny. Why should we?

5
00:00:23,521 --> 00:00:27,802
I mean humans 
are the only animals who really laugh.

6
00:00:27,802 --> 00:00:29,252
They can go,
“No, there’s a laughing hyena!”

7
00:00:29,252 --> 00:00:33,666
—No, that doesn’t count.
[Laughing]

8
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:34,564
Well, I’m just saying …

9
00:00:34,564 --> 00:00:37,733
So, humans, we laugh, 
we cry …

10
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:39,799
You can say, “Oh, animals wail!” 
That’s true,

11
00:00:39,799 --> 00:00:41,054
because they’re approaching human—

12
00:00:41,054 --> 00:00:44,095
they wail when their babies
are taken away and things like that.

13
00:00:44,095 --> 00:00:48,267
You start feeling.
So what we’re all about is feeling.

14
00:00:48,267 --> 00:00:50,118
Not just objective things …
We can say,

15
00:00:50,118 --> 00:00:54,565
“Oh, well we can make you
feel better with chemistry.”

16
00:00:54,565 --> 00:00:59,483
Better living through chemistry,
or as one author said,

17
00:00:59,485 --> 00:01:03,621
“There’s got to be more to life,
and the story of life,

18
00:01:03,621 --> 00:01:08,305
and the possibility of life;
then the narrative says,

19
00:01:08,305 --> 00:01:13,437
‘My chemicals were bad,
I fixed them.’”

20
00:01:13,437 --> 00:01:18,859
So the idea is just about 
chemical balances—

21
00:01:18,865 --> 00:01:23,813
happiness is nothing more 
than a particular type of chemical balance.

22
00:01:23,828 --> 00:01:29,400
The things that we’re really
hardwired to seek:

23
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:34,478
beauty, love, humour …

24
00:01:34,478 --> 00:01:38,577
I can’t prove to you 
that someone is beautiful.

25
00:01:38,577 --> 00:01:42,202
I can’t prove love even exists,
and statistically

26
00:01:42,202 --> 00:01:45,555
we could make a case 
that it doesn’t exist.

27
00:01:45,555 --> 00:01:49,014
And we could say, like they 
talk about the God delusion—

28
00:01:49,014 --> 00:01:51,792
we could write a book called
The Love Delusion.

29
00:01:51,792 --> 00:01:54,546
Why is everyone searching for this?
It that no one has it.

30
00:01:54,546 --> 00:01:58,170
They’re all lying to themselves.
It doesn’t really exist.

31
00:01:58,185 --> 00:02:01,601
But there’s an element 
with inside us 
 

32
00:02:01,601 --> 00:02:05,841
that can’t accept that 
that it doesn’t exist.

33
00:02:05,841 --> 00:02:12,877
And even in the face
of heavily anti-statistical evidence

34
00:02:12,877 --> 00:02:15,745
that you won’t get it,
you’re not experiencing it,

35
00:02:15,745 --> 00:02:18,947
we’ll still search for it.

36
00:02:18,947 --> 00:02:24,049
So it means really, as subjects
we’re in the situation:

37
00:02:24,049 --> 00:02:28,895
we’re spiritual subjects living and
navigating a mundane environment,

38
00:02:28,895 --> 00:02:32,390
searching for subjective inner fulfilment.

39
00:02:32,390 --> 00:02:37,507
So then it becomes obvious—
we need to repurpose ourselves

40
00:02:37,507 --> 00:02:41,405
in addressing that inner fulfilment.
When we try merely

41
00:02:41,405 --> 00:02:44,685
to acquire, control,
and consume objective things,

42
00:02:44,696 --> 00:02:48,525
it doesn’t produce the type of joy
that we’re seeking.

